text: The ReidOut is an American television talk show. It was hosted by Joy Reid. It premiered on the now-defunct America's Talking network in 1994 (as Politics with Chris Matthews) before moving on CNBC, and then to MSNBC, where it remained until its end in 2020. It primarily featured coverage of political issues and headlines, along with discussion from a panel of analysts and political figures.
